        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3927677635" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14144068111092747372">This is a brilliant theory and thesis about how crowds work and supportive literature has already been written that supports this thesis. I am very interested in group think and tribalism at the moment because I see so much of it online on social media. I want to know how it works. Many psychologist have read this work and often refer to it so it became important to read it. I will be rereading it after I finish several other current books who advance this thesis with their work in other areas, </span>
  <span id="freeText14144068111092747372" style="display:none">This is a brilliant theory and thesis about how crowds work and supportive literature has already been written that supports this thesis. I am very interested in group think and tribalism at the moment because I see so much of it online on social media. I want to know how it works. Many psychologist have read this work and often refer to it so it became important to read it. I will be rereading it after I finish several other current books who advance this thesis with their work in other areas, for example Jaron Lanier.<br /><br />The book is basically about crowds and behavior. How the group alters the social dynamics. I will come back to it soon and detail my review.</span>
