<div id="review_1904465647" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1904465647" />
    <a title="Shane" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8002827-shane"><img alt="Shane" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1595840756p2/8002827.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1904465647?book_show_action=true">Mar 03, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Shane" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Shane" href="/user/show/8002827-shane">Shane</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780140036169" href="/book/show/1787444.Crowds_and_Power">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8002827-shane?shelf=best-non-fiction">best-non-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1904465647" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4844315631194217714">A book written with an individual, literary sense of research (power) backed up by a litany of references from ancient times to the 1950s (crowd), this book is a paradox of prophesy and outdatedness that strikes a chord due to Canetti&apos;s excellent writing. Some of the borrowed descriptions of rituals and events in different cultures are fascinating, while Canetti&apos;s writing is strongest when it is metaphorical and descriptive. On rare occasions in this monumental book the writing gets slow or old-</span>
  <span id="freeText4844315631194217714" style="display:none">A book written with an individual, literary sense of research (power) backed up by a litany of references from ancient times to the 1950s (crowd), this book is a paradox of prophesy and outdatedness that strikes a chord due to Canetti's excellent writing. Some of the borrowed descriptions of rituals and events in different cultures are fascinating, while Canetti's writing is strongest when it is metaphorical and descriptive. On rare occasions in this monumental book the writing gets slow or old-fashioned, but 'Crowds and Power' is still a well of information and ideas that resonates today as much as when it was published.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4844315631194217714" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


